law.text:
When any statute providing for newspaper publication of an advertisement does not designate the person responsible for causing the publication to be made, the responsible person shall be:
Where the advertisement is of the filing of a petition or application, the person by whom the same is filed;
Where the advertisement is of an activity or action of:
An individual public officer, the officer himself;
A city, the city clerk if there be one; if not, the mayor;
A county, the county clerk;
A district, or a board, commission or agency of a city, county or district, the chief administrative or executive officer or agent thereof;
A court, the clerk thereof;
A state department or agency, the head thereof.
